10.3 Error Analysis
===================

The following functions and variables may be used to analyze the errors
of a syntax check.

 -- Variable: flycheck -current-errors

          Variable properties: Automatically becomes buffer-local when
          set.

     A list of all errors and warnings in the current buffer.

 -- Function: flycheck -count-errors errors

     Count the number of ERRORS, grouped by level..

     Return an alist, where each ITEM is a cons cell whose ‘`car'’ is an
     error level, and whose ‘`cdr'’ is the number of errors of that
     level.

 -- Function: flycheck -has-errors-p errors level

     Determine if there are any ERRORS with LEVEL.

 -- Function: flycheck -has-max-errors-p errors level

     Check if there is no error in ERRORS more severe than LEVEL.


